```

The polling approach works cross-platform but has a 15-second detection lag. On macOS, `NWPathMonitor` gives instant notifications. For a Rust CLI, polling is fine -- for a macOS GUI app (like Serena), use the native API. The `watch` channel pattern lets any part of your application subscribe to connectivity changes without polling.
